  "prompt": "Is the plant pictured below poison ivy?",
  "response": "I can\u2019t see images, but I can help you identify poison ivy! Poison ivy typically has three leaflets (often described as \"leaves of three, let them be\"). The leaflets can have smooth or slightly toothed edges, and the plant can vary in size and shape. In the spring, it may have a reddish tint, and in the fall, the leaves can turn a vibrant red. \n\nIf you describe the plant to me or provide more details, I might be able to help you determine if it's poison ivy. Always exercise caution when dealing with unknown plants!",
